# No personal paths in the repo

Never commit or suggest committing **machine-specific personal paths** or local-only filesystem identity.

## Forbidden in tracked files

- Absolute home paths: `C:\Users\<you>\...`, `/Users/<you>/...`, `/home/<you>/...`
- Hard-coded clone locations (e.g. `cd C:\Users\maxwa\AIDesktopSearch`)
- Real corpus / Documents paths that identify the developer’s machine beyond `%USERPROFILE%` / `$HOME` placeholders
- Local DB paths, absolute `AIDESKTOP_DB` / `AIDESKTOP_ROOT` values pointing at a personal folder

## Use instead

- “From the **repo root**” (no absolute `cd`)
- Env vars: `AIDESKTOP_ROOT`, `AIDESKTOP_DB`
- Portable placeholders: `%USERPROFILE%\...`, `$env:USERPROFILE`, `$HOME`, `<repo-root>`

```powershell
# BAD
cd C:\Users\maxwa\AIDesktopSearch
npm run dev

# GOOD
npm run dev   # run from your clone of the repo
```

## Before commit / README edits

If a path would only work on one person’s PC, rewrite it. Product branding in `app.config.json` (display name, company, `appId`) is fine when intentional — that is not a filesystem leak.
